2015年初，由[[寨卡病毒|寨卡病毒]]引发的[[茲卡熱|茲卡熱]]在巴西大规模[[流行病|流行]]，并传播到[[美洲|美洲]]、多个太平洋岛屿和东南亚<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.healthmap.org/zika/|title=Zika Map - Virus & Contagious Disease Surveillance|publisher=HealthMap|accessdate=2017-05-21|archive-date=2016-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821164455/http://www.healthmap.org/zika/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2016年1月，[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]宣布到该年底，病毒传播很可能遍及美国大部分地区<ref name="WHO sees Zika outbreak spreading">{{cite news |url=http://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-zika-idUSKCN0V30U6 |title=WHO sees Zika outbreak spreading through the Americas |work=Reuters |date=2016-01-25 |accessdate=2017-05-21 |archive-date=2016-01-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160125183847/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-zika-idUSKCN0V30U6 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2016年11月，世卫组织宣布寨卡疫情结束<ref name="WHO: Zika Virus No Longer International Emergency But Still a Threat">{{cite news |url=https://newsline.com/zika-virus-no-longer-international-emergency-still-threat/ |title=WHO: Zika Virus No Longer International Emergency But Still a Threat |work=Newsline |date=2016-11-21 |access-date=2018-02-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211072422/https://newsline.com/zika-virus-no-longer-international-emergency-still-threat/ |archive-date=2018-02-11 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

2016年2月，世卫组织宣布疫情为[[国际公共卫生紧急事件|国际公共卫生紧急事件]]。证据表明寨卡可致使新生婴儿畸形并患上精神疾病<ref name="WHO Summarizes Emergency Committee">{{cite web |url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2016/emergency-committee-zika-microcephaly/en/ |title=WHO Director-General summarizes the outcome of the Emergency Committee regarding clusters of microcephaly and Guillain–Barré syndrome |publisher=World Health Organization |date=2016-02-01 |accessdate=2016-02-02 |archive-date=2016-02-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203114521/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/statements/2016/emergency-committee-zika-microcephaly/en/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="The emergence of zika virus">{{cite journal |url=http://www.jgid.org/text.asp?2016/8/1/3/176140 |title=The emergence of zika virus as a global health security threat: A review and a consensus statement of the INDUSEM Joint working Group (JWG) |date=2016-02-11 |display-authors=3 |last=Sikka |first=Veronica |last2=Chattu |first2=Vijay Kumar |last3=Popli |first3=Raaj K. |last4=Galwankar |first4=Sagar C. |last5=Kelkar |first5=Dhanashree |last6=Sawicki |first6=Stanley G. |last7=Stawicki |first7=Stanislaw P. |last8=Papadimos |first8=Thomas J. |journal=Journal of Global Infectious Diseases |volume=8 |issue=1 |pages=3–15 |language=en |issn=0974-8245 |doi=10.4103/0974-777X.176140 |pmid=27013839 |pmc=4785754 |access-date=2020-10-07 |archive-date=2017-09-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170910145031/http://www.jgid.org/text.asp?2016%2F8%2F1%2F3%2F176140 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。受感染的孕妇可将病毒传播给胎儿，随后造成婴儿[[小头畸形|小头畸形]]和大脑严重变形<ref name="RasmussenJamieson2016">{{cite journal | first1=Sonja A. | last1=Rasmussen | url=http://www.nejm.org/doi/10.1056/NEJMsr1604338 | title=Zika Virus and Birth Defects — Reviewing the Evidence for Causality | last2=Jamieson | first2=Denise J. | last3=Honein | first3=Margaret A. | last4=Petersen | first4=Lyle R. | journal=New England Journal of Medicine | volume=374 | issue=20 | pages=1981–7 | issn=0028-4793 | doi=10.1056/NEJMsr1604338 | pmid=27074377 | date=2016-04-13 | access-date=2017-05-21 | archive-date=2020-09-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200929033820/https://www.nejm.org/doi/10.1056/NEJMsr1604338 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=CDC2016Cause>{{cite web|title=CDC Concludes Zika Causes Microcephaly and Other Birth Defects|url=http://www.cdc.gov/media/releases/2016/s0413-zika-microcephaly.html|website=CDC|accessdate=2016-04-14|date=2016-04-13|archive-date=2016-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160414173217/http://www.cdc.gov/media/releases/2016/s0413-zika-microcephaly.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="WHO SitRep Apr 7, 2016">{{cite web | url=http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/204961/1/zikasitrep_7Apr2016_eng.pdf?ua=1 | title=Zika Virus Microcephaly And Guillain–Barré Syndrome Situation Report | publisher=World Health Organization | date=2016-04-07 | accessdate=2016-04-08 | archive-date=2016-04-16 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160416041725/http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/204961/1/zikasitrep_7Apr2016_eng.pdf?ua=1 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。成人感染病毒会出现[[格林－巴利综合征|格林－巴利综合征]]<ref name="WHO SitRep Apr 7, 2016"/>。疫情爆发前，寨卡被认为是轻度传染病，大多数寨卡病毒感染症状是隐性的，使得断定病例准确个数非常困难<ref name="ITV28Jan2016">{{cite news | url=http://www.itv.com/news/update/2016-02-01/zika-epidemic-worse-than-thought-brazil-health-minister/ | title=Brazil Health Minister: Zika epidemic worse than thought | work=ITV News | date=2016-01-28 | accessdate=2016-02-01 | archive-date=2016-02-01 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201193204/http://www.itv.com/news/update/2016-02-01/zika-epidemic-worse-than-thought-brazil-health-minister/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。大约五个寨卡病毒感染病例，有一个是由寨卡热引发的，而这个引发[[发烧|发烧]]和[[疹|出疹]]症状的疾病又是少数的<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdc.gov/zika/symptoms/|title=Zika Virus|publisher=Centers for Disease Control and Prevention|accessdate=2017-05-21|archive-date=2016-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129165646/http://www.cdc.gov/zika/symptoms/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdc.gov/zika/symptoms/symptoms.html|title=Zika Virus|publisher=Centers for Disease Control and Prevention|accessdate=2017-05-21|archive-date=2016-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160824044146/http://www.cdc.gov/zika/symptoms/symptoms.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

病毒主要由一般在热带和副热带地区生存的[[埃及斑蚊|埃及斑蚊]]传播和分布在美国[[五大湖|五大湖]]地区的[[白纹伊蚊|白纹伊蚊]]传播<ref name="The global distribution of the arbovirus vectors">{{cite journal |url=http://elifesciences.org/content/4/e08347 |title=The global distribution of the arbovirus vectors ''Aedes aegypti'' and ''Ae. albopictus'' |date=2015-07-07 |display-authors=3 |last=Kraemer |first=Moritz U.G. |last2=Sinka |first2=Marianne E. |last3=Duda |first3=Kirsten A. |last4=Mylne |first4=Adrian Q.N. |last5=Shearer |first5=Freya M. |last6=Barker |first6=Christopher M. |last7=Moore |first7=Chester G. |last8=Carvalho |first8=Roberta G. |last9=Coelho |first9=Giovanini E. |journal=ELife |volume=4 |pages=e08347 |language=en |issn=2050-084X |doi=10.7554/eLife.08347 |pmc=4493616 |pmid=26126267 |access-date=2017-05-21 |archive-date=2016-12-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220204649/https://elifesciences.org/content/4/e08347 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。感染了寨卡的人可以将病毒转播给他们的性伴侣<ref name="The emergence of zika virus" /><ref name="Interim Guidelines for Prevention of Sexual Transmission">{{cite journal |display-authors=3 |first1=Alexandra M. |first3=Jo Ellen |first7=Lyle R. |journal=Morbidity and Mortality Weekly Report |last1=Oster |url=http://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/volumes/65/wr/mm6505e1.htm |title=Interim Guidelines for Prevention of Sexual Transmission of Zika Virus – United States, 2016 |last2=Brooks |first2=John T. |last3=Stryker |last4=Kachur |first4=Rachel E. |last5=Mead |first5=Paul |last6=Pesik |first6=Nicki T. |last7=Petersen |year=2016 |volume=65 |issue=5 |pages=120–121 |issn=0149-2195 |doi=10.15585/mmwr.mm6505e1 |pmid=26866485 |access-date=2017-05-21 |archive-date=2016-03-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160316083426/http://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/volumes/65/wr/mm6505e1.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="cdc1">{{cite web | url=http://www.cdc.gov/media/releases/2016/s0223-zika-guidance.html | title=CDC encourages following guidance to prevent sexual transmission of Zika virus | publisher=Centers for Disease Control and Prevention | work=CDC Newsroom | date=2016-02-23 | accessdate=2017-05-21 | archive-date=2016-02-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160227052140/http://www.cdc.gov/media/releases/2016/s0223-zika-guidance.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="nyttavernise">{{cite news |last1=Tavernise |first1=Sabrina |title=C.D.C. Investigating 14 New Reports of Zika Transmission Through Sex |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/24/health/zika-virus-sexual-transmission.html |accessdate=2016-02-24 |work=The New York Times |date=2016-02-23 |archive-date=2016-02-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160223215837/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/24/health/zika-virus-sexual-transmission.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

鉴于疫情将显著减少[[旅游|旅游]]，许多国家颁布了[[旅游警示|旅游警示]]<ref name="The emergence of zika virus" /><ref name="wsjtourism">{{cite news |last1=Kiernan |first1=Paul |last2=Jelmayer |first2=Rogerio |title=Zika Fears Imperil Brazil's Tourism Push |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/zika-fears-imperil-brazils-tourism-push-1454461138 |accessdate=2016-02-27 |work=The Wall Street Journal |publisher=Dow Jones & Company |date=2016-02-03 |archive-date=2016-02-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160226104129/http://www.wsj.com/articles/zika-fears-imperil-brazils-tourism-push-1454461138 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。更有国家直接建议孕妇延期生产，直到获知病毒及其对胎儿发育的影响<ref name="Zika virus triggers pregnancy delay calls">{{cite news |url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-35388842 |title=Zika virus triggers pregnancy delay calls |work=BBC News Online |date=2016-01-23 |accessdate=2017-05-21 |archive-date=2019-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190506050018/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-35388842 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。此外，疫情也引发民众担忧[[2016年夏季奧林匹克運動會|2016年里約奥運會]]上运动员和观众的健康安全<ref name="USAToday25Feb2016">{{cite news |last=Rogers |first=Martin |url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/olympics/2016/02/24/zika-virus-rio-world-health-organization/80858758/ |title=World Health Organization: Athletes should not fear Zika virus at Rio Olympics |work=USA Today |date=2016-02-25 |accessdate=2017-05-21 |archive-date=2020-09-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919080442/https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/olympics/2016/02/24/zika-virus-rio-world-health-organization/80858758/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="CNN12Feb2016">{{cite news |last=Vox |first=Ford |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/02/12/health/zika-olympics-threat |title=What real threat does Zika pose to the Rio Olympics? History has an answer |work=CNN |date=2016-02-12 |accessdate=2017-05-21 |archive-date=2016-04-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425232144/http://www.cnn.com/2016/02/12/health/zika-olympics-threat/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="USA cyclist Tejay van Garderen withdraws from Olympics over Zika virus">{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/jun/02/tejay-van-garderen-zika-olympics-cycling |publisher=The Guardian |website=www.theguardian.com |date=2016-06-02 |title=USA cyclist Tejay van Garderen withdraws from Olympics over Zika virus |accessdate=2017-05-21 |archive-date=2016-06-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603100441/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/jun/02/tejay-van-garderen-zika-olympics-cycling |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在巴西，寨卡疫情暴露医疗体系的结构性问题，尤其是公共卫生服务和基础卫生设施方面<ref>{{cite news |last1=Buriti |first=Renata |title=Virus shines light on structural problems |url=http://www.dandc.eu/en/article/zika-proves-brazil-needs-better-sanitation-and-health-services |accessdate=2016-11-28 |work=D+C, Development and Cooperation |date=2016-10-30 |archive-date=2016-11-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161118050903/http://www.dandc.eu/en/article/zika-proves-brazil-needs-better-sanitation-and-health-services |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

