2016年1月，为应对寨卡病毒疫情，巴西国家生物安全委员会宣布批准在全国范围内投放更多基因改良的埃及斑蚊<ref name="How mosquitoes with ‘self-destruct’ genes" />。此前，{{le|牛津昆虫技术|Oxitec}}于2015年7月发布在巴西[[茹阿泽鲁|茹阿泽鲁]]地区进行的所谓“自我限制”蚊子的测试结果，抗击登革热、基孔肯雅蚊症和寨卡病毒。据他们总结，测试地区的蚊子数量减少到九成以上<ref name="How mosquitoes with ‘self-destruct’ genes">{{cite news |last=Kim |first=Meeri |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/to-your-health/wp/2016/01/29/heres-how-gm-mosquitos-with-self-destruct-genes-could-save-us-from-zika-virus/ |title=How mosquitoes with 'self-destruct' genes could save us from Zika virus |work=The Washington Post |date=2016-01-29 |accessdate=2017-05-28 |archive-date=2016-01-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129163604/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/to-your-health/wp/2016/01/29/heres-how-gm-mosquitos-with-self-destruct-genes-could-save-us-from-zika-virus/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Oxitec mosquito works to control Aedes">{{cite web |url=http://www.oxitec.com/press-release-oxitec-mosquito-works-to-control-aedes-aegypti-in-dengue-hotspo/ |title=Oxitec mosquito works to control Aedes aegypti in dengue hotspot |publisher=Oxitec |work=Press release |date=2015-07-02 |access-date=2017-05-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203083908/http://www.oxitec.com/press-release-oxitec-mosquito-works-to-control-aedes-aegypti-in-dengue-hotspo/ |archive-date=2016-02-03 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name="OlsonCarvalho2015">{{cite journal | display-authors=3 | first1=Ken E. | url=http://journals.plos.org/plosntds/article/asset?id=10.1371%2Fjournal.pntd.0003864.PDF | title=Suppression of a Field Population of ''Aedes aegypti'' in Brazil by Sustained Release of Transgenic Male Mosquitoes | last2=Carvalho | first2=Danilo O. | last3=McKemey | first3=Andrew R. | last4=Garziera | first4=Luiza | last5=Lacroix | first5=Renaud | last6=Donnelly | first6=Christl A. | last7=Alphey | first7=Luke | last8=Malavasi | first8=Aldo | last1=Olson | last9=Capurro | first9=Margareth L. | journal=PLOS Neglected Tropical Diseases | year=2015 | volume=9 | issue=7 | pages=e0003864 | issn=1935-2735 | doi=10.1371/journal.pntd.0003864 | pmid=26135160 | pmc=4489809 | access-date=2017-05-28 | archive-date=2016-03-14 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160314085900/http://journals.plos.org/plosntds/article/asset?id=10.1371%2Fjournal.pntd.0003864.PDF | dead-url=no }}</ref>。经基因改造的雄性蚊子与雌性在野外交配并传播自我限制的基因，导致后代在进入成年期之前死亡，从而减少当地蚊子数量<ref name="How mosquitoes with ‘self-destruct’ genes" /><ref name="OlsonCarvalho2015" />。2016年1月，该项技术被圣保罗[[皮拉西卡巴|皮拉西卡巴]]镇用于抗击寨卡病毒<ref name="NYT">{{cite news|last1=Pollack|first1=Andrew|title=New Weapon to Fight Zika: The Mosquito|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/31/business/new-weapon-to-fight-zika-the-mosquito.html?_r=0|accessdate=2016-03-16|publisher=New York Times|date=2016-01-30|archive-date=2016-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203154347/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/31/business/new-weapon-to-fight-zika-the-mosquito.html?_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2016年2月1日，世卫组织宣布目前的寨卡病毒疫情为国际公共卫生紧急事件<ref name="WHO Summarizes Emergency Committee" /><ref name="NYT – W.H.O. Declares Zika Virus">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/02/health/zika-virus-world-health-organization.html |title=W.H.O. Declares Zika Virus an International Health Emergency |work=[[纽约时报|The New York Times]] |date=2016-02-01 |last1=Tavernise |first1=Sabrina |last2=McNeil, Jr. |first2=Donald G. |accessdate=2017-05-28 |archive-date=2016-02-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160208085615/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/02/health/zika-virus-world-health-organization.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，巴西总统颁布政令，派遣地方和联邦害虫防治员到有需要的私人财产，预防或消除埃及斑蚊在该国的疫情<ref name="Decree No. 8662">{{cite web |url=https://planalto.gov.br/ccivil_03/_ato2015-2018/2016/decreto/d8662.htm |title=Decreto Nº 8.662 |publisher=Palácio do Planalto, Presidência da República |date=2016-02-01 |accessdate=2016-02-04 |language=pt |trans-title=Decree No. 8662 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160302044801/https://www.planalto.gov.br/ccivil_03/_ato2015-2018/2016/decreto/d8662.htm |archivedate=2016-03-02 }}</ref>。

部分专家支招抗击寨卡病毒时，提出应培育并投放基因经改良的蚊子，防止它们传播病原体，或者让蚊子感染[[沃尔巴克氏体|沃尔巴克氏体]]，抑制病毒传播<ref name="GlobeNews">{{cite news | first1=Kate | last1=Kelland | url=http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/who-backs-trials-of-genetically-modified-mosquitoes-to-fight-zika/article29297605/ | title=WHO backs trials of genetically modified mosquitoes to fight Zika | work=The Globe and Mail | date=2016-03-18 | accessdate=2016-03-19 | archive-date=2016-03-18 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160318223119/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/who-backs-trials-of-genetically-modified-mosquitoes-to-fight-zika/article29297605/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="The Best Weapon for Fighting Zika">{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-02-04/as-zika-virus-goes-global-scientists-breed-infected-mosquitoes |title=The Best Weapon for Fighting Zika? More Mosquitoes |work=[[彭博新聞社|Bloomberg News]] |date=2016-02-04 |author=Jason Gale |accessdate=2017-05-28 |archive-date=2017-04-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170406044831/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-02-04/as-zika-virus-goes-global-scientists-breed-infected-mosquitoes |dead-url=no }}</ref>。另一项建议用的技术是利用放射性{{le|昆虫不育术|Sterile insect technique|使雄性幼虫绝育}}，好让他们交配无法产出后代<ref name="UN Readies Nuclear Solution">{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-02-12/un-readies-nuclear-weapons-to-destroy-the-zika-virus |title=UN Readies Nuclear Solution to Destroy the Zika Virus |work=Bloomberg Business |date=2016-02-12 |last=Tirone |first=Jonathan |accessdate=2017-05-28 |archive-date=2017-05-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170511084034/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-02-12/un-readies-nuclear-weapons-to-destroy-the-zika-virus |dead-url=no }}</ref>。雄性蚊子并不咬人或传播疾病<ref name="Mosquito Biology">{{cite web |url=http://www.mimosq.org/mosquitobiology/mosquitobiology.htm |title=Mosquito Biology |publisher=Michigan Mosquito Control Association |accessdate=2016-02-23 |archive-date=2013-03-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130330125526/http://www.mimosq.org/mosquitobiology/mosquitobiology.htm |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

2月，巴西联邦政府派遣占总体60%的约220000名[[巴西军事|军人]]到350个[[市镇_(巴西)|市镇]]，警告或教育居民如何减少蚊子繁殖面积<ref name="Brasil destina 60% das suas Forças Armadas">{{cite news |last=Martín |first=María |url=http://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2016/02/13/politica/1455383958_196275.html?id_externo_rsoc=FB_CM |title=Brasil destina 60% das suas Forças Armadas na luta contra um mosquito |language=pt |trans_title=Brazil deploys 60% of its armed forces in the fight against mosquitoes |work=El Pais |location=Río de Janeiro |date=2016-02-13 |accessdate=2017-05-28 |archive-date=2016-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160222194434/http://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2016/02/13/politica/1455383958_196275.html?id_externo_rsoc=FB_CM |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2016年2月10日，全球30多个健康机构发布联合声明，共享美洲寨卡病毒疫情及未来公共卫生紧急事件的数据和结果<ref name="Data sharing in public health emergencies">{{cite news |url=http://www.wellcome.ac.uk/About-us/Policy/Spotlight-issues/Data-sharing/Public-health-emergencies/index.htm |title=Data sharing in public health emergencies |work=Wellcome Trust Blog |date=2016-02-10 |accessdate=2016-02-21 |archive-date=2016-03-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301163530/http://www.wellcome.ac.uk/About-us/Policy/Spotlight-issues/Data-sharing/Public-health-emergencies/index.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。声明加强了世卫组织于2015年9月发布声明中的相似共识<ref name="WHO – Developing global norms for sharing data">{{cite web |url=http://www.who.int/medicines/ebola-treatment/blueprint_phe_data-share-results/en/ |title=Developing global norms for sharing data and results during public health emergencies |publisher=World Health Organization |date=September 2015 |accessdate=2016-02-21 |archive-date=2016-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160220214453/http://www.who.int/medicines/ebola-treatment/blueprint_phe_data-share-results/en/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。声明呼吁所有数据应尽可能地快和广泛地自由查阅<ref name="Sharing data during Zika">{{cite web |url=http://blog.wellcome.ac.uk/2016/02/10/sharing-data-during-zika-and-other-global-health-emergencies/ |title=Sharing data during Zika and other global health emergencies |work=Wellcome Trust Blog |date=2016-02-10 |accessdate=2016-02-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160220204353/http://blog.wellcome.ac.uk/2016/02/10/sharing-data-during-zika-and-other-global-health-emergencies/ |archive-date=2016-02-20 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

2016年2月，[[谷歌中国|谷歌]]宣布向[[联合国儿童基金会|联合国儿童基金会]]捐资100万美元，抗击寨卡病毒，让专业人员协助决定接下来受影响的地区<ref name="Google donates $1M to help fight Zika virus spread">{{cite news |url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/health/ct-google-zika-virus-20160303-story.html |title=Google donates $1M to help fight Zika virus spread |work=The Baltimore Sun |date=2016-03-03 |accessdate=2017-05-28 |archive-date=2016-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328074224/http://www.baltimoresun.com/health/ct-google-zika-virus-20160303-story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==治疗手段==
虽然寨卡的治疗手段尚未明确，但疫苗目前正在研发。三种疫苗设计抗击寨卡病毒的可信度高。科学家在恒河猴身上进行测试，人体试验于2016年底开展<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hamzelou|first1=Jessica|title=Zika vaccine trials begin – but fears remain over virus’s impact|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/2104167-zika-vaccine-trials-begin-but-fears-remain-over-viruss-impact/|website=New Scientist|accessdate=2016-10-12|archive-date=2016-10-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161012160457/https://www.newscientist.com/article/2104167-zika-vaccine-trials-begin-but-fears-remain-over-viruss-impact/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

这种预防性治疗有希望，但需时多年才能广泛使用<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bednarczyk|first1=Robert|title=Why a Zika vaccine is a long way off|url=http://theconversation.com/why-a-zika-vaccine-is-a-long-way-off-63804|website=the conversation|accessdate=2016-10-12|archive-date=2016-10-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161012153829/http://theconversation.com/why-a-zika-vaccine-is-a-long-way-off-63804|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

疫苗生产办法有三种，一种是无活性寨卡病毒测试，另外两种是检测病毒遗传密码复制品。在疫苗接种试验期间有望完全抵抗病毒，不会有明显副作用。

英国专家明确表示，疫苗开发耗时颇久。[[威斯敏斯特大学|威斯敏斯特大学]]高级讲师和病毒学家艾德·怀特博士（{{lang|en|Dr.Ed Wright}}）表示：“目前开发的所有疫苗离正式许可投入大范围公众使用还有几年时间。”[[诺丁汉大学|诺丁汉大学]]病毒学教授乔纳森·巴尔（{{lang|en|Jonathan Ball}}）：“我们知道疫苗在小白鼠身上起了作用，现在研究人员已经表明，非人灵长类动物也需免受寨卡病毒感染的保护。下一步是要看疫苗是否安全，科学家希望开始初期人体试验来解决问题<ref name="ZikaEarlyPromise">{{cite news|access-date=2016-08-08|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/health-36975088|title=Zika vaccines show early promise|work=BBC News|date=2016-08-04|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108133232/https://www.bbc.com/news/health-36975088|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”

西雅图生物技术公司Kineta正在积极开展治疗，并获得[[国立卫生研究院_(美国)|美国国立卫生研究院]]{{le|国家过敏与传染病研究所|National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases}}资金支持。Kineta行政总裁肖恩·艾多纳托博士（{{lang|en|Dr.Shawn Iadonato}}）在声明中表示：“我们渴望扩大寨卡病毒广谱抗病毒药物检测，因为它们对登革热和[[西尼罗河病毒|西尼罗河病毒]]等黄病毒的疗效强大，具备长期开发的潜质<ref name = "KinetaZikaFunding">{{cite news|access-date=2016-08-08|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/seattle/blog/health-care-inc/2016/08/kineta-awarded-funding-to-test-zika-treatment.html|title=Kineta awarded funding to test Zika treatment|work=Puget Sound Business Journal|date=2016-08-05|archive-date=2016-08-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817232505/http://www.bizjournals.com/seattle/blog/health-care-inc/2016/08/kineta-awarded-funding-to-test-zika-treatment.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”

截至2016年7月26日，Inovio Pharmaceuticals公司在其评估公司寨卡DNA疫苗的多中心一期试验中，提供了首个实验对象。除了美国FDA之前宣布批准研究外，加拿大卫生部健康产品食品股也批准研究，研究将在迈阿密、费城和魁北克市的临床地点进行。首阶段的开放标签剂量范围研究中，40人健康的成年志愿者在Inovio专有的真皮内DNA递送装置的管控下，评估GLS-5700的安全性、耐受性和免疫原性。在临床前测试中，这种合成疫苗在小型和大型动物模型中诱导出强大抗体和T细胞反应（抗病毒感染必须的免疫反应）<ref name = "InovioTrials">{{cite news| access-date=2016-08-08| url=https://globenewswire.com/news-release/2016/07/26/858976/0/en/Inovio-Pharmaceuticals-Doses-First-Subject-in-Zika-Vaccine-Clinical-Trial.html| title=Inovio Pharmaceuticals Doses First Subject in Zika Vaccine Clinical Trial| work=Inovio Pharmaceuticals| date=2016-07-26| archive-date=2016-07-30| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160730213134/https://globenewswire.com/news-release/2016/07/26/858976/0/en/Inovio-Pharmaceuticals-Doses-First-Subject-in-Zika-Vaccine-Clinical-Trial.html| dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==争议==
有些遏制寨卡病毒传播的手段极具争议性。Oxitec公司在巴西释放的“自我限制”蚊子把致命基因传给后代，遭到环保组织批评，他们担心释放新的蚊子菌株会破坏生态系统。短期内的关注点是蚊子数量的下降可能会影响其他物种种群。支持者声称，“自我限制”蚊子的环境影响微乎其微，成为目标的蚊子仅此一种，而且基因改造过的蚊子对于食肉动物而言仍然是安全的。Oxitec产品开发经理德里克·尼莫（{{lang|en|Derric Nimmo}}）形容这个过程是“拿手术刀带走埃及伊蚊，不留一丝影响<ref name="washingtonpostSelfDestruct">{{cite news | access-date=2016-03-20 | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/to-your-health/wp/2016/01/29/heres-how-gm-mosquitos-with-self-destruct-genes-could-save-us-from-zika-virus/ | title=How mosquitoes with 'self-destruct' genes could save us from Zika virus | work=The Washington Post | date=2016-01-29 | last=Kim | first=Meeri | issn=0190-8286 | archive-date=2016-01-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129163604/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/to-your-health/wp/2016/01/29/heres-how-gm-mosquitos-with-self-destruct-genes-could-save-us-from-zika-virus/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。”由于埃及伊蚊在巴西是进口[[入侵物种|入侵物种]]，部分专家希望它的根除不会影响环境。然而，其他环保人士强调，消亡整个物种的长期后果难以估量<ref name="cbsSupportGrows">{{cite news | access-date=2016-03-20 | url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/genetically-modified-mosquitoes-zika-virus-fight/ | title=Support grows for genetically modified mosquitoes in Zika fight | work=CBS News | date=2016-02-16 | archive-date=2016-03-19 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319043545/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/genetically-modified-mosquitoes-zika-virus-fight/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

政府建议孕妇推迟分娩也留有争议。[[人权|人权]]和[[生育权|生育权]]组织认为这些建议不负责任，很难遵循，因为只有妇女才有避孕的任务，尽管这样做的控制效果微乎其微<ref name="timeAvoidPregnancy">{{cite news | access-date=2016-03-20 | url=http://time.com/4197318/zika-virus-latin-america-avoid-pregnancy/ | title=Governments: Avoid Pregnancy Because of Zika. But How? | work=Time | date=2016-01-29 | last=Alter | first=Charlotte | archive-date=2016-03-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160312160232/http://time.com/4197318/zika-virus-latin-america-avoid-pregnancy/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。2012年的一项研究表明，[[拉丁美洲|拉丁美洲]]和[[加勒比地区|加勒比地区]]56%的怀孕是意外的（全球意外怀孕率为40%）<ref name="Intended and Unintended Pregnancies Worldwide in 2012 and Recent Trends">{{cite journal | last1 = Sedgh | first1 = Gilda | last2 = Singh | first2 = Susheela | last3 = Rubina | first3 = Hussain | url = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1728-4465.2014.00393.x/epdf | title = Intended and Unintended Pregnancies Worldwide in 2012 and Recent Trends | journal = Studies in Family Planning | volume = 45 | issue = 3 | pages = 301–314 | date = Sep 2014 | doi = 10.1111/j.1728-4465.2014.00393.x | pmid = 25207494 | pmc = 4727534 | access-date = 2017-05-28 | archive-date = 2018-03-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180309044402/http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1728-4465.2014.00393.x/epdf | dead-url = no }}</ref>。在[[罗马天主教会|罗马天主教会]]占主导地位的[[萨尔瓦多|萨尔瓦多]]等地区，[[生育控制|避孕药具]]的使用可能受限<ref name="washingtonpostElSalvador">{{cite news | access-date=2016-03-20 | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the_americas/as-zika-virus-spreads-el-salvador-asks-women-not-to-get-pregnant-until-2018/2016/01/22/1dc2dadc-c11f-11e5-98c8-7fab78677d51_story.html | title=As Zika virus spreads, El Salvador asks women not to get pregnant until 2018 | work=The Washington Post | date=2016-01-22 | last=Partlow | first=Joshua | issn=0190-8286 | archive-date=2016-03-19 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319211656/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the_americas/as-zika-virus-spreads-el-salvador-asks-women-not-to-get-pregnant-until-2018/2016/01/22/1dc2dadc-c11f-11e5-98c8-7fab78677d51_story.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。大部分地区的反[[堕胎|堕胎]]法律导致大部分地区女性一旦怀孕便无追索权。除了[[疟疾|疟疾]]广泛流行的三个国家法属圭亚那、圭亚那和乌拉圭和三个允许堕胎畸形胎儿的国家哥伦比亚、墨西哥和巴拿马外，大部分地区只允许堕掉[[强奸|强奸]]、[[乱伦|乱伦]]产生或危机母体健康的婴儿。在萨尔瓦多，一切堕胎皆违法<ref name="timeAvoidPregnancy" />。

2016年2月5日，[[联合国人权事务高级专员办事处|联合国人权事务高级专员办事处]]敦促拉美国家政府考虑废除其避孕和堕胎政策，强调“维护人权对于有效公共卫生应对措施至关重要”<ref name="Upholding women’s human rights">{{cite news | access-date=2016-03-20 | url=http://www.ohchr.org/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=17014&LangID=EN | title=Upholding women's human rights essential to Zika response — Zeid | publisher=United Nations | work=News and Events | date=2016-02-05 | archive-date=2016-04-09 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160409125842/http://www.ohchr.org/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=17014&LangID=EN | dead-url=no }}</ref>。2016年2月16日，梵蒂冈谴责联合国呼吁采取行动，认为这是对寨卡危机的“不法回应”，强调“儿童小头畸形症诊断不是判处死刑的授权<ref name="zenitHolySee">{{cite news | access-date=2016-03-20 | url=https://zenit.org/articles/holy-see-on-zika-virus-international-community-should-exercise-due-diligence-but-not-panic/ | title=Holy See on Zika Virus: International Community Should Exercise Due Diligence, But Not Panic | work=Zenit | date=2016-02-17 | archive-date=2016-04-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160404142432/https://zenit.org/articles/holy-see-on-zika-virus-international-community-should-exercise-due-diligence-but-not-panic/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。”

2016年2月18日，访问拉丁美洲后，教宗[[方济各|方济各]]表示在寨卡病毒疫情的病例中，“避孕并非绝对的罪恶”。他的说话引发人们猜测在预防寨卡病毒方面，使用避孕措施受道德允许<ref name="washingtonpostPope">{{cite news | access-date=2016-03-20 | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/acts-of-faith/wp/2016/02/17/mexico-confirms-zika-virus-cases-in-pregnant-women-as-pope-francis-exits-the-country/ | title=Pope Francis suggests contraception could be permissible in Zika fight | work=The Washington Post | date=2016-02-17 | last=Bailey | first=Sarah Pulliam | last2=Boorstein | first2=Michelle | issn=0190-8286 | archive-date=2016-03-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160312214800/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/acts-of-faith/wp/2016/02/17/mexico-confirms-zika-virus-cases-in-pregnant-women-as-pope-francis-exits-the-country/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

